highlightText: Steps to Install Presto on a local machine (Linux)  From a high-level, below are the required steps to get Presto up and running on your local machine  #### 1 Setup the Presto Server - Download and install the Presto server tarball - Create the required directories - Create and configure 3 property files     - nodes.properties     - jvm.config     - config.properties  #### 2.
In large enterprise clusters, it's recommended to use one machine as the coordinator and another machine as the worker as this enhances the performance of the overall system.
